          "pause": true,
          "displayType": "poster",
          "buttonOnMobile": false,
          "label": "<p>When inserting a chest drain into an intercostal space, where should the needle </p>",
          "x": 30,
          "y": 30,
          "width": 40,
          "height": 25,
          "libraryTitle": "Multiple Choice",
          "action": {
            "library": "H5P.MultiChoice 1.16",
            "params": {
              "question": "<p>When inserting a chest drain into an intercostal space, where should the needle be placed to avoid the neurovascular bundle?</p>",
              "answers": [
                {
                  "text": "<div>Just below the lower border of the upper rib</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>This is the danger zone — the VAN bundle (vein, artery, nerve) hugs the costal groove on the underside of each rib. Inserting here will strike the bundle.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Just above the upper border of the lower rib</div>",
                  "correct": true,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Correct. By hugging the top of the rib below, your needle passes well beneath the neurovascular bundle of the rib above. The rib itself shields the vessels in the groove.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Through the middle of the intercostal space</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The middle of the space is risky — the collateral branch and main neurovascular bundle are both close. Always aim just above the lower rib.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Directly through the costal cartilage anteriorly</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Cartilage is tough, painful to traverse, and not the standard insertion site. Chest drains go through the safe triangle, just above the lower rib.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                }
              ],
              "overallFeedback": [
                {
                  "from": 0,
                  "to": 50,
                  "feedback": "Remember: the VAN bundle (Vein, Artery, Nerve) lies in the costal groove on the underside of each rib. Always insert just above the lower rib of the space, never just below the upper one."
                },
                {
                  "from": 51,
                  "to": 100,
                  "feedback": "Excellent clinical reasoning. VAN bundle = Vein, Artery, Nerve in the costal groove of the upper rib — so always insert just above the lower rib."
                }
              ],
              "behaviour": {
